==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Molest
<hw>Mo*lest"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Molested</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Molesting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F. <ets>molester</ets>, L.
<ets>molestare</ets>, fr. <ets>molestus</ets> troublesome, fr.
<ets>moles</ets> a heavy mass, load, burden. See 3d
<er>Mole</er>.]</ety> <def>To trouble; to disturb; to render uneasy; to
interfere with; to vex.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They have <qex>molested</qex> the church with needless
opposition.</q> <rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To trouble; disturb; incommode; inconvenience;
annoy; vex; tease.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Molest</ent>⟦br⟧

